## 9. Agent Onboarding Protocol (Do This First, Every Time)

Before writing any code on a task, an agent must:

```
1. Read the relevant src/ files for the stage you're working on
2. Read two adjacent/completed stage files to understand existing patterns
3. Check outputs/checkpoints/ for any saved model state relevant to your stage
4. Summarize your understanding:
   - "The existing featurization pipeline produces X shaped tensors"
   - "The current train/val/test split is done in split.py using temporal ordering"
   - "The GNN encoder outputs a Z-dimensional latent vector"
5. Only then begin implementation
```

**If you skip steps 1–4, stop and go back. Never write code against assumptions
about data shapes or interfaces — verify them first.**

